<HEADLINE> Three Killed, Five Missing in Avalanches in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and
five others went missing in avalanches which broke out Saturday
morning in Gorkha district, western Nepal, the official RSS news
agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The avalanches which occurred in three villages buried five
houses and 20 yaks were also missing, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The Budhigandaki river nearby was blocked for about an hour,
damaging three wooden bridges, the news agency added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
