<DOCNO> XIE19990104.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Top Leader Calls for Campaign Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's ruling Communist Party
chief Le Kha Phieu said Sunday that Vietnam will launch a
campaign against bureaucracy and corruption in the new year.
</P>
<P>
The general secretary was speaking at a meeting with mediamen
here on the occasion of the new year, according to Vietnam News
Agency (VNA).
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Phieu regarded "bureaucracy and corruption in
the state apparatus as the biggest concerns", VNA said.
</P>
<P>
However, the top leader believed that the party, state and
people will "sweep away the evils with drastic measures".
</P>
<P>
"Members of the Politburo and PCC, party and state officials
will practice criticism and self-criticism and the party building
work will be combined with the fighting against bureaucracy and
corruption as well as the making of the party and state apparatus
to be clean and strong," Phieu said.
</P>
<P>
The party leader stressed that it should be "more determined to
dismiss degraded members from the party" so as to "build the party
strong in ideology, morality and lifestyle".
</P>
<P>
"The party revamping work will be implemented continuously in
many years", Phieu said.
</P>
<P>
The general secretary pointed out that "the regional financial
crisis is not the main reason of the lower growth rate of
Vietnam's national economy", but "mainly the subjective reasons
and weakness in management and control of the economic
structure".
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have not mobilized all our internal resources and
people's strength yet. The state apparatus is still bureaucratic,
cumbersome and less effective."
</P>
<P>
Vietnam should continue speeding up administrative reform to
make the state administrative system more effective, Phieu noted,
adding that the restructuring must be done step by step and all
social issues arisen during the process should be settled.
</P>
<P>
The party leader also said practicing thrift and fighting
wastefulness and bureaucracy must be strictly implemented.
</P>
<P>
He urged the entire party and people to practice thrift so as
to have more investments in boosting production and improve the
living conditions of the poor people.
</P>
<P>
Phieu held that the people's right to mastery must be
truthfully practiced and called for reorganizing patriotic
emulation movements.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the journalists' role, the party leader stressed
that "as  fighters on the cultural and ideological front,
journalists have the tasks to disseminate the party's lines and
policies and to get in close touch with the daily life in order to
thoroughly understand realities to help the party and state work
out appropriate policies."
</P>
<P>
He added that journalists are also the people's voice and the
voice of justice, who "take an active part in the fight against
bureaucracy and corruption". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
