<HEADLINE> Arab League Chief Says Preparation Essential for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Arab League Secretary General
Esmat Abdel-Meguid said on Sunday that good preparation is
essential for an Arab summit aimed at discussing critical issues
in the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Consultations are underway among Arab leaders in this respect,
Abdel-Meguid told a press conference held here with Boutros Boutros
Ghali, secretary general of the Francophone Organization.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome holding this summit," which is agreed upon by the
Arab leaders, Abdel-Meguid said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Kuwait has informed him about its decision to
attend the Arab foreign ministers meeting scheduled to be convened
on January 24.
</P>
<P>
There is no sign at present that the meeting will be delayed
once again, he said.
</P>
<P>
Arab countries planned to convene a foreign ministers meeting
last Wednesday to discuss the recent U.S-British military attack
on Iraq. Requested by Kuwait, Saudi Arabia and other Gulf
countries, the meeting was put off last Monday to January 24.
</P>
<P>
Boutros Ghali said the Francophone Organization could cooperate
with the Arab League to alleviate the sufferings of the Iraqi
people.
</P>
<P>
"What matters now is the Iraqi people who suffer the
consequences of the crippling economic and political sanctions,"
Boutros Ghali said.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council imposed the trade embargo
on Iraq in 1990 after its invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
He said he discussed with Abdel-Meguid economic, diplomatic and
cultural cooperation between their two organizations, adding that
he has invited Arab League to attend a Francophone conference on
investments and foreign trade to be held in Monaco in April.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid has agreed to send an observer to the conference,
Boutros Ghali said, stressing that both organizations have the
desire to cooperate for the interests of their member states.
</P>
</TEXT>
