<HEADLINE> Angolan Govt Army Inflicts Losses on UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Information from the military showed that over 700 UNITA soldiers have
been killed in the war fields in Huambo and Bie provinces in the recent
three weeks.
These victories on the side of the government army has eased situation in
Kuito city whose various airports are again in use.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in a fighting in the neighboring Benguela Province, the army
captured 16 tanks, 11 anti-tank missiles, 16 mortars and more than 300
automatic weapons.
</P>
<P>
Joao de Matos, chief of the general staff of the Angolan army, said in
Kuito
Sunday that the army will continue its counter-offensive in all parts of
the
country until all places occupied by UNITA are returned to government hands.
</P>
</TEXT>
