<HEADLINE> Southwest China Bridge Collapse Kills Twelve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- A Qijiang County bridge in the
 southwest China municipality of Chongqing collapsed today killing
 at least 12 pedestrians and leaving an as yet undetermined number
of people missing.
</P>
<P>
The 180 meter long by seven meter wide Rainbow Bridge collapsed
at 18:30 (Beijing time) this evening dumping over 20 armed police
soldiers and an undetermined number of civilians into the Qijiang
River.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities launched immediate rescue efforts but reports
indicate only a few victims had been rescued by press time.
</P>
<P>
The steel bridge was erected by a private contractor in
February 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
