<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Deputy PM to Visit Jordan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Deputy Prime
Minister Abdel Aziz Al-Dekheel will pay a visit to Jordan Tuesday,
marking a further step to the normalization of Kuwaiti-Jordanian
ties.
</P>
<P>
Al-Dekheel, also Minister of State for Cabinet Affairs, will
meet with Jordan's Crown Prince Hassan and convey him a letter on
bilateral ties from his Kuwaiti counterpart Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Salem Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
The deputy prime minister will be the highest-ranking Kuwaiti
official to visit Jordan since the Kuwaiti-Jordanian ties soured
after Iraq's invasion of Kuwait in 1990, when Amman, along with a
few other Arab states, sided with Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
A rapprochement process between the two sides began in May
1997 when Kuwait declared it would like to "improve ties with all
Arab countries except Iraq".
</P>
<P>
Since then the two countries have exchanged a number of
middle-level visits.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sabah
Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah said on Sunday that he had invited his
Jordanian counterpart Abdul Ilah al-Khatib to visit Kuwait, the
strongest signal so far that the ties between the two countries
will be resumed very soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
