<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Starts Historic Journey to Birembo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KAMPALA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni has
started a journey through some districts to commemorate the battle of
Birembo which took place in western Kibale district in 1985 during the
liberation struggle of his National Resistance Movement (NRM).
</P>
<P>
A press release issued from the President's Office Monday afternoon
said the journey will take the president westward to districts of Mpigi,
Mubende and Kibale.
</P>
<P>
On the first leg of his historic journey, Museveni addressed a rally at
a primary school in Mpigi district close to the capital Kampala where he
thanked the people for supporting the liberation struggle that brought
constitutional governance into the country.
</P>
<P>
He informed the people that his journey is aimed at rekindling the
process of rural reconstruction. So he will walk through the area and use
the chance to generate ideas on how to reconstruct and develop the area,
especially the area affected during the liberation war.
</P>
<P>
The process of rebuilding the country must proceed systematically, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Turning to the specific focus of his tour, the President said he wants
to see that the people improve their homestead incomes. He appealed to them
to undertake economic activities that can improve their living standards.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government has constructed the core of the economy,
built a strong army and won a political battle through the ballot box. The
government now has the capacity to begin rural construction, Museveni added.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
