<HEADLINE> Laos, China Agree to Cooperate in Mineral Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Lao government and the Yunnan
Geology and Mineral Industry Co. Ltd. of China have reached an
agreement on mineral exploration and production in Xieng-Ngeun
district, Luang Prabang province, the official Lao news agency KPL
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan company has won a 26-year concession and will make a
total investment of 2.74 million U.S. dollars in the mineral
exploration and extraction in an area of 392 square kilometers in
Xieng-Ngeun.
</P>
<P>
The mineral exploration will kick off this month.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony of the agreement in Vientiane on December
31 was attended by Bountiem Phitsamay, minister to the prime
minister's office and Zhao Jiahua, the Chinese ambassador to Laos.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
