<HEADLINE> Hongkong Telecom Cuts International Call Tariffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom announced
Monday that it was cutting international call tariffs by up to 30
percent and would provide money-back guarantees on its long
distance service quality.
</P>
<P>
The company said it had obtained regulatory approval to
introduce new tariffs for all popular destinations including the
Chinese mainland except Guangdong, which is priced as low as 6.70
HK dollars (86 U.S. cents) per minute.
</P>
<P>
The money back guarantee applies to the company's 001 and 0060
long distance services, and covers such areas as service
provision, call quality and connection time.
</P>
<P>
If customers use Hongkong Telecom and encounter poor call
quality such as noise or echo, the company will give two minutes
off that call if it was made using 001, and one minute off if it
was made using 0060, the company said.
</P>
<P>
Roy Wilson, executive director of the Hongkong Telecom, said:
"Hongkong Telecom is ready to meet the challenges of the new
market environment. We are going to compete aggressively by
continuing to provide our customers with first class services and
benefits at highly competitive prices." 
</P>
</TEXT>
