<HEADLINE> Shanghai Lotteries Produce 23 Millionaires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Two Shanghai residents became
millionaires in a lottery drawing held earlier this evening.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three Shanghainese has gained millionaire status over
the past six month after winning the "Graceful Shanghai"
lotteries.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that more than 60 million lottery
tickets, or an average four ticket for each resident, have been
sold during the period. The tickets sell for five yuan each and
offer holders a change to win one million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The latest lottery issue increased the accumulated fund to over
100 million yuan, including 20 million yuan earmarked for the
construction of a modern welfare center for children.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai held its first lottery in 1987, with total sales
through the end of last year approaching 400 million yuan. Related
funds have been used to finance more than 1,000 welfare projects
in the city.
</P>
</TEXT>
