Iraqi National Assembly (parliament) Ajeel Jalal Ismaail on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ismaail and his delegation have just returned home after a
four-day visit to Tehran at the invitation of Iranian Majlis
(parliament).
</P>
<P>
He told the Iraqi News Agency that the Iranian parliament
decided to release 400 Iraqi POWs in appreciation of the Iraqi
parliamentary delegation's visit, apart from what was agreed on by
the technical committees between Iraq and Iran.
</P>
<P>
Ismaail said Iran would set free another 376 Iraqi POWs in the
coming days according to the agreement between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
He said the Iraqi delegation held talks with Iranian
parliamentary members as well as governmental officials on
expanding relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the U.S.-British air strikes
against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain raided Iraq for four consecutive
nights on December 16-19 in an operation code-named "Desert Fox,"
which was condemned by the Iranian government.
</P>
<P>
The issue of POWs has long stood on the way of normalization
between Iraq and Iran, two former foes that fought an eight-year
war in the 1980s. 
</P>
