<HEADLINE> Security Tightened in Islamabad after Killings in Punjab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Police in the twin cities of
Islamabad and Rawalpindi have tightened security outside the
mosques and Imambargahs after an attack by unknown terrorists at
an Imambargah in central Punjab Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Police will guard outside the mosques and Imambargahs in the
twin cities in uniform as well as in plain clothes especially
during the prayer times for the protection of the faithful,
according to the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
The government has also directed the police and district
administration throughout the country to keep a vigil on the
terrorists and their subversive activities, APP said.
</P>
<P>
The police have also beefed up the security in the main markets
and bazaars in Rawalpindi and Islamabad where business activities
have increased for Eid shopping.
</P>
<P>
Police in Punjab and Islamabad have also started strict
checking of the suspected vehicles at various entry and exit
points of the twin cities of Rawalpindi and Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said 16 Shia worshippers were killed and more
than 20 others injured during an armed attack by a group of
unidentified terrorists Monday morning at an Imambargah near the
central Punjab town of Muzaffargarh. 
</P>
