<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Party School of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and Intel joined
hands today to provide information technology lectures to Chinese
officials.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 mid-level government officials from throughout
the nation and military officers attended the CPC Party School
Intel Technology Day held in Beijing, the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Intel China President Jim Jarrett presented a welcoming address
via a computer link from Santa Clara, California.
</P>
<P>
The event marked the first time the Party School has cooperated
with a foreign company in sponsoring a training session for
officials. The school is the party's Highest training center for
mid-level and high-ranking CPC and government officials.
</P>
<P>
An official from the instruction department said the school
offers courses on Maxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng
Xiaoping Theory, as well as required core courses related to
advanced science and technology, law, finance, management, culture
and ideological trends.
</P>
<P>
Participants in today's session attended lectures and
discussion sessions during which they raised questions concerning
E-commerce, the Internet, venture capital and various other
issues. An Intel official attending the session praised the
officials for their understanding of information technology and
eagerness to learn. 
