<HEADLINE> Publishing Business Booms in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 4 (Xinhua) -- With Macao's upcoming return to
the motherland, more books and periodicals have been published in
Macao and book sales have mounted accordingly.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that for sale are some 300 kinds of books and
periodicals turned out by local publishing houses.
</P>
<P>
Publishers attributed the boom to the fact that people in the
mainland areas of China and other parts of the world want to know
more about the laws, investment environment and tourism of Macao
and the daily life of local residents.
</P>
<P>
In addition to government-funded publications in Macao,
publishers from the mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan have plans to
produce more books on Macao in the coming year. 
