<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Imposes Curfew, Closure on Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai ordered Monday morning the Israel Defense Force
(IDF) to impose an immediate curfew on and a closure of
Hebron, following attacks on Jewish settlers in the city, the
army said.
</P>
<P>
Unknown gunmen opened fire Monday morning at a bus the
Jewish settlers were riding in Hebron, and two women settlers
were hit by bullets, one of them seriously, the army said.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister is receiving constant reports of the
situation in Hebron and directing the actions of the IDF and
other Israeli security forces in and around the city, the army
added.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister has ordered the immediate curfew and
closure of the city to prevent the situation in Hebron from
further worsening, the army added.
</P>
<P>
The army believed that the gunmen were Palestinians and the
IDF and other Israeli security force are conducting a manhunt
for the attackers, the army said.
</P>
<P>
Hebron is situated in the south of the West Bank. The
majority population of the city are Palestinians, but there are
45 Jewish families living in the city with heavy protection of
the IDF.
</P>
<P>
Clashes and confrontations occurred quite often in the city
between the Palestinians and Jewish settlers in the past.
</P>
<P>
Last August, Israeli settler Rabbi Shlomo Ra'anan was stabbed
to death at his home in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
