<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Elections Period Starts in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The election period for the
upcoming national and municipal elections of Turkey, scheduled to
be held on April 18 this year, starts Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the decisions made by the Supreme Board of
Elections, during the beginning of the election period, the media
is prohibited from partisan broadcasting in favor or against any
political party or candidate.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for political parties to inform the board of the
criteria and methods they will employ in defining their
candidates is Friday.
</P>
<P>
Public workers who plan to announce their candidacy or who
will be presented as candidates, must submit their resignations
from their posts by next Monday at the latest.
</P>
<P>
Those who want to enter the elections as independent
candidates must apply to the provincial election councils by
February 24.
</P>
<P>
The announcement of temporary lists of deputy candidates will
start on March 1 via radio and television stations and in the
Official Gazette.
</P>
<P>
The election campaign will begin on April 8 and end on April
17 and campaign speeches by political parties on radio and
television stations will start on April 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
