<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1,924 Forest Fires Occurred in Turkey in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 6,743 hectares of
forests were burnt in 1,924 fires in Turkey in 1998, local Daily
News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to data from the Turkey's Forestry General
Directorate, carelessness and negligence resulted in 976 fires
which caused the loss of 2,880 hectares of forested area, and 278
forest fires and the loss of 988 hectares of forest were the
results of arson.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that electrical power lines malfunctions,
traffic accidents and lightning are cited as other causes of
the forest fires.
</P>
<P>
The province of Mugla in western Turkey topped the list of
provincial fire occurrence with 240 forest fires while the
southwestern province of Antalya had the severest damage from
fires, losing 1,425 hectares of forest.
</P>
<P>
In the past 10 years, 18,808 forest fires have resulted in the
loss of 124,466 hectares of forested area in Turkey, said the
paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
