<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Tamil Rebels Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Sunday confronted the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE)
rebels in separate clashes in the north of the country, killing
seven rebels, a military spokesman said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops observed a rebel
bunker line ahead of defenses in Mankulam and engaged the rebels
with rocket-propelled grenades and mortars, killing three rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident, government troops conducted a small group
operation forward of defenses east of Ampakamam and killed three
rebels, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
Also on Sunday, the government troops operating forward of
defenses at Paranthan sniped and killed one rebel, the spokesman
added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a war against the government
for a state of its own in the north and east of the country since
1983. So far nearly 60,000 people are reported to have been killed
in the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
