<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Clamps Down on Illegal Computer Shops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Ten computer game shops involved
in gambling or violations of intellectual property rights, have
been closed down in Haikou, capital of the Island Province of
Hainan, and authorities have confiscated 146 computers.
</P>
<P>
Under the guise of providing computer training or consultation,
the owners and operators of the shops were actually engaged in
illegal activities such as offering customers the use of smuggled
or pirated software, many of them pornographic and violent films
in compact disks.
</P>
<P>
According to an official of the Haikou bureau for industry and
commerce, these practices violate intellectual property rights and
are simple disguises for gambling dens, which are detrimental to
the development of young people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
