<HEADLINE> Ancient Stone Axe Found in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- A stone axe dating back some 4,500
years has been found by a farmer in Huanglong County in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Xiubin, a farmer from Matizhang village, was leveling a
stretch of ground when he spotted the black axe measuring 46 cm
long and 24 cm wide and weighing ten kg.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists say that the axe is the first of its kind found
in China and it has been handed over to the local relics
administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
