<HEADLINE> China's Sixth Mutual Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Puhui Mutual Fund had an
offering on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange worth two billion yuan at
a unit price of 1.01 yuan last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is China's sixth mutual fund this year.
</P>
<P>
Regulations limit the amount of the fund used for securities
and bonds to not lower than 80 percent of the fund's net value.
</P>
<P>
The new fund was started by Shenzhen's Guoxin Securities
Company and is managed by the Penghua Fund Management Co. Ltd.,
with the Bank of Communications acting as trustee.
</P>
<P>
By December 18, the Kaiyuan, Jintai, Xinghua, Anxin, and Yuyang
funds had net increases ranging from 3.2 percent to 8.1 percent.
</P>
