<HEADLINE> Significant Growth for South China's Industrial Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 4 ( Xinhua) -- Despite the negative impact
of the Asian financial crisis, industrial production in south
China's Guangdong Province witnessed a high rise last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the added value of Guangdong's industry grew on 1997's
figures by 11.5 percent to 350.8 billion yuan, with industrial
output jumping by 13.5 percent to 1,187.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Rapid development in basic industries largely accounted for the
overall industrial growth. The turnover of posts and
telecommunications rose by 21.74 percent to 36.8 billion yuan in
1998, while the number of passengers carried by the transport
sector hit 596 million, up 20 percent. Power generation reached
103.4 billion kwh, an increase of 5.4 percent from 1997.
</P>
<P>
The year 1998 also witnessed a substantial rise in exports of
manufactured goods. In particular exports to Europe, North
America, Latin America and Oceania surged by 23.7 percent, 23.8
percent, 33.9 percent and 44.5 percent respectively but exports to
the Asian region were sluggish and only grew by 5.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
To boost it's industrial growth, Guangdong shut down a number
of loss-making enterprises in such sectors as mining and sugar
production, while within the textile industry production was
slashed with 113,000 spindles destroyed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
