<TEXT>
<P>
At 09:00 (00:00 GMT), the euro was quoted at 132.58 yen, down
0.22 yen from the 132.80 yen rate set last Thursday by the
European Commission. Tokyo is the first major financial market to
begin trading in the euro.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the euro was quoted at 1.1754-1758 dollars, higher
than the 1.16675 dollars rate set Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said euro-yen trading was quiet as both exporters and
importers were cautious.
</P>
<P>
