<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- China will send four acrobatics
troupes abroad and will take part in three acrobatics competitions
in January, two in Monaco and one in Switzerland, the Culture
Ministry announced here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Li Gang, director of the Ministry's External
Cultural Relations Bureau, acrobatics and Peking opera and folk
dance and music have been the most popular performance items
Chinese artists staged outside China for the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
China has won gold medals in acrobatics in international
contests and last year won the highest award at competition in
Monte Carlo.
</P>
<P>
January's other exchange activities include a visit by a
Israeli cultural delegation, Richard Marx's concerts in Beijing
and Shanghai, a series of cultural activities by Saudi Arabia, and
an African art exhibition.  
</P>
</TEXT>
