<HEADLINE> Two Killed, Two Wounded in Los Angeles Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Two armed security guards
were shot to death while another two guards were critically
wounded Sunday after a shooting occurred at an apartment complex
near downtown Los Angeles, police said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the security guards argued with a man at the
New Wilmington Arms Complex, a block-long residential quarter
about 20 miles (32 kilometers) south of this second largest U.S.
city, before the man fired at them.
</P>
<P>
Police Lieutenant Danny Sneed said the complex is in a area
plagued by gang and drug-related violence, and the shooter
appeared to be a man who "frequents the building" but it wasn't
clear if he was a resident of the building.
</P>
