<HEADLINE> Fujimori Names Joy Way as Peru's New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joy Way, now the president of congress, will be sworn in on
Monday or Tuesday to replace Alberto Pandolfi and preside over
the cabinet, said Fujimori.
</P>
<P>
The move was seen as the beginning of a broader cabinet
reshuffle, as Fujimori had said that he would form a new
ministerial team for the New Year.
</P>
<P>
Diplomats here said the president was likely to make further
changes in cabinet as part of his efforts to help boost the
country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Once an engineer, Joy Way has been in public service for
years after graduation from the Peru Super Administration High
School and then earning a master degree of economy in
Massachusetts, the United States.
</P>
<P>
He was in charge of planning at the Ministry of Industry,
Trade and tourism from 1969 to 1974, and promoted to serve as
general director of International Negotiations at the ministry
from 1974 to 1979.
</P>
<P>
Joy Way also worked as advisor of the United Nations Special
Program for Assistance to Bolivia and main advisor for the
promotion of export of the Andes Group in the Organization of
American States.
</P>
<P>
He became vice president of Congress from 1993 to 1995, when h
e helped charted the country's new marco plans for politics and
economy, and then elected president of the top legislature in
July 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
