<HEADLINE> China Working Out Yangtze River Flood-Control Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- China is working on a plan for
flood control that takes into consideration all sections of the
Yangtze River, but focuses on the middle and lower reaches.
</P>
<P>
It involves a comprehensive plan to harness the river and
emphasizes flood diversion, with consideration given to improving
floodwater storage capacity.
</P>
<P>
The new plan is based on one originally drawn up by the State
Council in 1990, which played a major role in the flood control
campaign last summer, but which needed to be brought up to date.
</P>
<P>
The new plan makes use of new materials, ideas, and technology
for both flood control and environmental protection, analysts
say.  
</P>
