<DOCNO> XIE19990104.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh City Polls to Be Held in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Elections to 139 municipalities in
Bangladesh will be held on February 23-25 and polls to the
country's four city corporations in late March or early April this
year, the Election Commission said.
</P>
<P>
The Election Commission made the decision at a meeting here on
Sunday, but the schedule of the elections for the 139
municipalities would be announced in the middle of this month, an
Election Commission official told Xinhua on Monday.
</P>
<P>
There are 182 municipalities in Bangladesh, but the February
elections would not take place in 43 of them for various reasons.
The tenure of elected councils is not over in seven
municipalities, and there are cases over 25 and border disputes in
19 of the municipalities.
</P>
<P>
According to a court order, the municipality elections have to
be held by March 19.
</P>
<P>
The tenure of the 139 municipalities ended in February 1998,
but the elections were deferred one year because of a writ
petition against a certain amendment to the electoral law.
</P>
<P>
Under the amended provision, the government would enjoy the
right to appoint a bureaucrat to run the municipalities for the
period between the expiry of the tenure of an elected body and the
take-over by another elected body.
</P>
<P>
A specific date for the city corporation elections was yet to
be decided. Officials said the Election Commission had a plan to
hold the corporation polls in Dhaka, Chittagong, Rajshahi and
Khulna with a brief break after the municipality elections.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 summit (Developing Eight) would be held in Dhaka on
March 1-2, and the secondary school certificate examinations would
start on March 4 and continue to weeks. "So we are planning to
hold the city corporations elections at the end of March or early
April," Secretary of the Election Commission Abdullah Harun Pasha
said.
</P>
<P>
The last municipal polls in Bangladesh were held on January 30,
1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
