<HEADLINE> Encyclopedia of Bangladesh to Be Out by 2002 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Banglapedia, an Encyclopedia of
Bangladesh in ten volumes both in English and Bangla, will come to
light in 2002, leading English newspapers here reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Bangapedia, a 100-million-taka (about 2.06 million U.S.
dollars) project of the Asiatic Society of Bangladesh (ASB), will
encompass the whole range of knowledge of the Bangladeshi people
and their culture and civilization from the pre-history times to
date, ASB president Professor M. Harunur Rashid was quoted as
saying in Dhaka Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Encyclopedia of Bangladesh has been designed as a national
reference work, research and information tool for scholars,
professionals, students and other general users, he said.
</P>
<P>
Encyclopedias in English are available in plenty, sources from
ASB noted, adding that only one or two have been compiled in
Bangla, and their lives and usefulness were short-lived for one
reason or another.
</P>
<P>
Twelve selected scholars from different disciplines have
already written the outline of the encyclopedia and another 65
scholars have been selected to scrutinize the draft, according to
the sources.
</P>
<P>
The encyclopedia is expected to contain a minimum of 10,000
entries to be contributed by more than 1,000 scholars from both
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
There is also a plan to preserve the Encyclopedia, when
completed, on a CD-Rom, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
