<HEADLINE> Myanmar Warns Against Loss of Sovereignty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lieutenant-General
Tin Oo has called on the people to oppose and prevent the
situation which can cause the nation to lose its sovereignty and
plunge into the life of a vassal or a satellite nation of
neo-colonialist powers.
</P>
<P>
Tin Oo, second secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council, made the call at an inaugural ceremony of a
newly-built dam in Mandalay division on Sunday without naming the
colonialists.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for the people to keep a wary eye on
"reactionaries," charging them with taking a head-on collusion
course and heading for conflicts.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that building of a modern and developed nation
is not for a single person or a single group, but for the
interests of all the national people.
</P>
<P>
He called on the people to work in perfect union to build a new
nation with goodwill to bring about benefit to the entire nation.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been accusing foreign neo-colonialists of
interfering its internal affairs and attempting to endanger its
sovereignty, calling for opposing and crushing those who rely on
external elements and try to jeopardize the stability of the state
and progress of the nation.  
</P>
