<HEADLINE> Mafia Boss Nabbed in Southern Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 3 (Xinhua) -- An Italian Mafia clan boss accused
of ordering nine murders was arrested Sunday in the country's
southern region of Calabria after being at large for over a year.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Cordi, one of Italy's most wanted fugitives, evaded
capture during a police sweep in October 1997 that put an end to
a long and bloody feud between two Mafia clans based in Calabria.
</P>
<P>
Cordi served as a politician in the crime-ridden town of Locri
in Calabria before taking over his clan's leadership in the wake
of his brother's assassination in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
He is believed to have ordered nine murders between 1994 and
1997, setting off a full-scale gang war that claimed seven lives
in seven months of 1997. 
</P>
