<HEADLINE> Work Begins on Major Meridian Tires Project in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Yinchuan Rubber Plant in
the capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region,
one of China's 500 largest industrial manufacturers, has commenced
construction of a new facility which will produce 300,000 sets of
steel belted meridian tires annually.
</P>
<P>
The project, a key part of China's technological improvement
program, is expected to transform the plant into the largest
radial tire producer in northwest China. It is to be completed in
the year 2001.
</P>
<P>
The overall project will be completed within two years at an
estimated cost of 600 million yuan, including an overseas
investment of over 29.28 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The plant plans to increase is annual sales volume by 544
million yuan and profits by 85 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
China initiated the research of meridian tires in the 1960s and
currently has an annual production capacity of 16 million sets.
</P>
<P>
The plant has a current annual production capacity of 2.2
million sets of meridian tires with 238 specifications.  
</P>
