<HEADLINE> Coal Mine Explosion Kills Six People in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 3 (Xinhua) -- An explosion at a coal mine in
Donbass, eastern Ukraine, killed six miners and injured another
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The blast took place when a group of miners were working
underground in the mine, one of the oldest in the area, the
Ukrainian Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
This was the third largest deadly event of the kind in the
country since April last year, when 63 people were killed and 51
others injured in a mine explosion.
</P>
<P>
In August 1998, another explosion caused the death of 24 min
ers.
</P>
<P>
Aging equipment and poor safety measures were blamed for the
explosions.
</P>
<P>
A total of 350 people were killed in 1998 in separate
accidents in the country's coal mining industry, said the
Ukrainian Interfax report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
