<HEADLINE> 30 Gold Miners Killed in Pongkor, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 miners at the Mt.
Pongkor gold mine in Bogor, West Java province of Indonesia, were
believed to be killed when the shafts in which they were working
caved in last Saturday, Antara News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Three days of incessant downpours had contributed to the cave
in of the shaft, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Until Sunday afternoon, only nine bodies of the victims had
been recovered, Bogor police chief Lieutenant colonel Ferial Manaf
said.
</P>
<P>
Reliable sources said the gold mine accident in the Cepu/Kompa
block was the third biggest catastrophe after a similar major
accident by the end of November 1998 killing 15 miners. In July
1998 18 people were buried alive in an accident.
</P>
<P>
The gold mine in Pongkor is a substitute to the one in Cikotok,
Banten, where its gold deposits had practically been depleted.
</P>
<P>
An official estimated that some 1,500 illegal miners were
operating in the mine. 
