<HEADLINE> Kasai Takes Lead in Four Hills Ski Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 3 (Xinhua) -- Noriaki Kasai took the lead in
the Four Hills ski jumping meeting in Innsbruck, Austria, on
Sunday after winning for Japan their first World Cup win of the
season on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
German sensation Martin Schmitt, who was the previous leader,
jumped poorly and finished 13th with distances of 107.0 and 96.50
meters.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old German, a new face who won six of the nine
events he has contested this season, is now third in the Four
Hills standings behind Kasai and Finland's Janne Ahonen.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Kasai, whose only other victory in a Four Hills
competition was in Garmisch six years ago, soared to jumps of
109.50 and 108.00 meters for his seventh career win.
</P>
<P>
Ahonen finished in second place with two jumps registering 108
.50 meters but he clinched the lead in the overall World Cup
standings after 11 events.
</P>
<P>
Hideharu Miyahira jumped 108.0 and 107.50 metres for third
place on a sunny day in the Tyrolean provincial capital and
Japanese team mate Masahika Harada was fourth.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's event is the third event of the renowned Four Hills
series. The last event will be staged at Bischofshofen next
Wednesday. 
</P>
