<HEADLINE> over 3,700 Rallies Held in Indonesia Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia witnessed over 3,700
rallies in various places across the country in 1998, according to
a police year-end report.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest number of rallies in the country over the
past three decades, the Jakarta Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Students took the lion's share as rally organizers. According
to police data, students staged 1,995 demonstrations, followed by
non-governmental organizations with 1,287 rallies and workers with
496.
</P>
<P>
As the capital, Jakarta recorded the largest number with 434
student rallies, 277 non-governmental organizations and 107 worker
protests.
</P>
<P>
Two other places that saw many students rallies in 1998 were
Central Java province (174) and West Java province (145).
</P>
<P>
The police also said the biggest number of worker rallies was
recorded in Central Java province (59) and West Java province
(49).
</P>
<P>
It was also announced that in 1998 the country witnessed 48
cases of rioting in many cities, including Jakarta (23) and North
Sumatera, Central and West Java (each with three riots). 
</P>
