<HEADLINE> Norhteastern Chinese Province Promotes Use of Farm Machines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Liaoning Province has
been stepping up efforts to promote the use of farm machinery for
agricutural production.
</P>
<P>
The province began its agricultural development strategy in the
mid-1980s and has put forward preferential policies to support
farm machinery development.
</P>
<P>
Some 70 percent of the ploughing is now done with farm
machinery, and 40 percent of the seeding is done by machines. The
province has been spending 10 million yuan annually improving
mid-sized and small tractors and has improved nearly 2,000 big
tractors.
</P>
<P>
About three billion yuan worth of machinery is being used for
agricultural production and farmers here have put more than 160,000
tractors in use.
</P>
<P>
The increased use of farm machinery helped the province save
more than 27 million kg in seeds and add more than 300 million kg
to its grain output last year. 
</P>
