<HEADLINE> Pakistan President Expresses Grief over Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's President Rafiq
Tarar expressed grief Sunday over the bomb blast near Raiwind,
about 30 kilometers south of Punjab's provincial capital of
Lahore.
</P>
<P>
In his message, the President condemned this heinous act of
terrorism and hoped that the culprits will soon be taken to task.
</P>
<P>
At least three people were killed and four others injured
Sunday morning when a bomb blasted at the bridge on the dual
carriageway from Lahore to Raiwind.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said that Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif was due to
travel along the road about five minutes later. However, the
sources said that it is too early to draw any connection.
</P>
<P>
Security has been tightened and a search is underway for the
culprits, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
